  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DRC-supported YRCS Primary Health Centres (IPACT)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">BRC will channel its support to Output&#xC2;&#xA0;2 of&#xC2;&#xA0;DRC&#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2122;s&#xC2;&#xA0;IPACT project&#xC2;&#xA0;(Integrated Programme for Affected Communities Transformation). 
The project&#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2122;s&#xC2;&#xA0;overall&#xC2;&#xA0;objective&#xC2;&#xA0;is to meet the immediate humanitarian needs in&#xC2;&#xA0;water, hygiene, health and psychosocial support&#xC2;&#xA0;of IDPs and vulnerable communities in Yemen.&#xC2;&#xA0;
Output 2 focuses on&#xC2;&#xA0;access to&#xC2;&#xA0;primary healthcare and community health services&#xC2;&#xA0;provided at YRCS Primary Health Centres (PHCs) to IDPs and vulnerable households in two target communities&#xC2;&#xA0;(Raymah al-Jibaan&#xC2;&#xA0;and&#xC2;&#xA0;Sayoun)&#xC2;&#xA0;
The project will provide those PHCs with medicines, consumables, equipment, running costs and staff/volunteer incentives according to YRCS&#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2122; standard package of support. If identified as a need, further repair or rehabilitation works may also be provided.</narrative>
  </description>
